## üöÄ Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Python 3.8+
- Anthropic API key

### Quick Start

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/your-username/claude-safeguards-framework.git
cd claude-safeguards-framework

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Start all components
./launcher.py
```

### Interactive Session

```bash
# Start an interactive Claude session with safeguards
./launcher.py --client
```

## üìä Configuration

All configuration is centralized in `config/safeguards_config.json`:

- Set alert thresholds
- Configure monitoring settings
- Customize detection patterns
- Enable/disable child safety features

## üíª Usage

### In Your Code

```python
from safeguards_aware_client import SafeguardsAwareClient

async def main():
    client = SafeguardsAwareClient(api_key="your_api_key")
    await client.connect_to_monitor()
    
    response = await client.get_completion("Hello, Claude!")
    print(response)
    
    await client.close_monitor_connection()

if __name__ == "__main__":
    import asyncio
    asyncio.run(main())
```

